report.name: Unknown Collaborator
report.description: This report shows which of the outside collaborators are not in your user_mapping of GitHub login to Internal Employee login.

report.name: Unknown Members
report.description: This report shows which of the organization members are not in your user_mapping of GitHub login to Internal Employee login.

report.name: Document Report
report.description: This report shows you *.txt and *.md files in your repositories. Useful for reviews by documentation writers.

report.name: License Report
report.description: This report shows you the repositories that the licensee project GitHub uses is unable to either find or identify.

report.name: Binary File Report
report.description: Uses the Linux file command to identify if a file is binary. Empty files and images are filtered out of the list.

report.name: Wiki-Enabled Repositories
report.description: This report shows repositories that have their wikis turned on.

report.name: Empty Repositories
report.description: This report shows repositories that GitHub is reporting as zero-sized.

report.name: Unchanged Repositories
report.description: This report shows repositories that have not had any changes since the day they were created.

report.name: Open Issues with no comments
report.description: This report shows open issues from the community with no comments.

report.name: Open PRs with no comments
report.description: This report shows open pull requests from the community with no comments.

report.name: Label Count Summary
report.description: This report shows the number of open issues and pull requests for a configured list of standard labels.

report.name: Label Summary
report.description: This report shows the labels in use, and how many issues + prs, open or closed, are in each.

report.name: Average Issue Close Time
report.description: This report shows the average time each repo takes to close issues

report.name: Average Pull Request Close Time
report.description: This report shows the average time each repo takes to close pull requests
